The paper deals with the problem of determining Nash equilibrium in win-lose bimatrix games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The techniques used in the paper are primarily graph theoretic, involving structural characterizations of minor-closed families, which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
